    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>mental health professionals... they just don't get it. they talk about \"managing\" the pain or \"coping mechanisms,\" but it's like trying to put out a forest fire with a water pistol. it doesn't actually change the fact that every single second is just agony. it feels less like a medical problem and more like a design flaw in my life. how am i supposed to \"cope\" with something that never, ever goes away?",
